According to a survey, the perfect time to have a drink is 5:30 p.m. on a Saturday.
The summer heatwave has increased consumption in more difficult British pubs, but put more pressure on restaurant chains.
Pubs and bars experienced 2.7 percent growth during July, but restaurant consumption fell 4.8 percent according to the figures.
