Pubs and bars specializing in beverages were the ones with the best results with increases in consumption exceeding the reductions experienced by restaurants.
Pubs specializing in food also suffered from the sun, though not as dramatically as restaurant operators.
It’s like people just want to go out and drink.
In controlled pubs and bars, beverage consumption increased by 6.6 percent during the month, and food consumption decreased by 3 percent.
Paul Newman, an employee at RSM, said: “These results are a continuation of the trend that has been taking place since the end of April.
