The warm and long summer could not have come at a worse time for the catering business and time will be in charge of saying whether the moderation of temperatures experienced during August will provide the much-needed respite for the sector.
Total sales growth in pubs and restaurants, including new openings, was 2.7 percent during July, reflecting the slowdown in brand launches.
The UK pubs, bars and restaurants industry’s sales indicator “Coffer Peach Tracker Industry” collects and analyzes performance data from 47 operating groups with combined profits of more than 9 billion pounds and is considered the industry benchmark.
